87.8	Anton_Chekhov	Anton Chekhov	Anton Pavlovich Chekhov was a Russian physician, dramatist and author who is considered to be among the greatest writers of short stories in history. His career as a dramatist produced four classics and his best short stories are held in high esteem by writers and critics. Chekhov practiced as a doctor throughout most of his literary career: "Medicine is my lawful wife", he once said, "and literature is my mistress."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Anton_Chekhov_1889.png/220px-Anton_Chekhov_1889.png
